HEADWORD: Daybook
<hw>Day"book`</hw> <pr>(d⟦amac⟧"b⟦oocr⟧k`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
journal of accounts; a primary record book in which are recorded the
debts and credits, or accounts of the day, in their order, and from
which they are transferred to the journal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

